\key{Strength} allows you to carry more and to hit harder. Add the
bonus to your to-hit rolls and to your damage rolls when using
\emph{melee weapons}.

\key{Dexterity} allows you to aim better and to better avoid attacks.
Add the bonus to your to-hit roll when using \emph{ranged weapons}
(but not to your damage rolls) and subtract the bonus from your
\hyperref[key:To-Hit]{armor class} (lower is better).

\key{Constitution} determines your health. Add the bonus to every
\hyperref[key:Hit Points]{hit die} (but never reduce a hit die below 1).

\key{Intelligence} determines your education. If you have a positive
bonus, it indicates how many extra \hyperref[key:Languages]{languages}
you speak.

\key{Wisdom} determines how much in tune with the world you are, and
how well immortals \hyperref[key:Reaction Roll]{react} to you. Add the
bonus to your \hyperref[key:Saving Throw]{saving throws}.

\key{Charisma} determines how well other mortals
\hyperref[key:Reaction Roll]{react} to you, how many
\hyperref[sec:followers]{followers} you can have (4 + your bonus) and
their \hyperref[key:Morale Check]{morale} (7 + your bonus).

\newthought{Choose your \index{Class}class}.

\hyperref[sec:fighter]{Fighter}\marginnote{\emph{What slaughter haunts
    your dreams? Whom do you hope to meet again in hell?}}: you can
fight well; you will be able to use magic swords; this is the simplest
character to play

\hyperref[sec:magicuser]{Magic User}\marginnote{\emph{Who or what
    taught you sorcery? Why does it damn you?}}: you can memorize the
\hyperref[sec:spells]{spells} in your spell book but you cannot fight
very well; you may be weak at first but if you survive, you will be
very powerful

\hyperref[sec:thief]{Thief}\marginnote{\emph{What do you love about
    adventure? Who taught you your tricks?}}: your skills will improve
with time; surprise your enemies and deal double damage

\hyperref[sec:elf]{Elf}\marginnote{\emph{What do you love and hate
    about humans? What inhuman thing will you do or refrain from
    doing, again and again?}}: you can memorize the
\hyperref[sec:spells]{spells} in your spell book and you can fight
well but you will advance very slowly; you can see in the dark; elves
can live forever; you need a minimum intelligence of 9

\hyperref[sec:dwarf]{Dwarf}\marginnote{\emph{What feud curses your family? How come your
    parents wanted a child?}}: you are small but hardy and you can fight
well; you sometimes know things about underground constructions; you can
see in the dark; you need a minimum constitution of 9

\hyperref[sec:halfling]{Halfling}\marginnote{\emph{Why did your
    parents let you go? How do you get over the lack of home and
    family?}}: you are even smaller than dwarves and you are always
barefoot; you can hide well and you are good at throwing and shooting
things; you are harder to hit by giants; halflings are nimble; you
need a minimum dexterity of 9 \marginnote{Questions adapted from
  \href{https://githyankidiaspora.com/2018/12/19/questions-and-hex-describe/}{Judd
    Karlman}.}

